# All variables are optional. With nothing set, the example uses the current
# canonical Node.js executable (`process.execPath`), so no external CLI is required.

# Absolute canonical path of the real coding CLI to invoke as the Fleet worker.
# Bare names and host PATH lookup are intentionally rejected. Defaults to the
# current Node.js executable (`process.execPath`).
# A2AMESH_CLI_FLEET_COMMAND=

# Name of an environment variable that already holds a provider API key for
# that CLI. Only the *name* goes here (credentialPolicy: 'env-ref') - the
# example never reads or writes the key value itself, and only this single
# named variable is forwarded to the child process.
# A2AMESH_CLI_FLEET_API_KEY_ENV=

# Override the sandboxed working directory the CLI runs in. Defaults to a
# fresh temporary directory created for each run.
# A2AMESH_CLI_FLEET_WORKSPACE=
